Ever the detective, Marcellus deduces what happened the night Tova''s son disappeared. And now Marcellus must use every trick his old body can muster to unearth the truth for her before it''s too late...

Shelby Van Pelt''s debut novel is a reminder that sometimes taking a hard look at the past can help uncover a future that once felt impossible.', 'A widowed night cleaner at an aquarium befriends a clever giant Pacific octopus named Marcellus, who narrates parts of the story with witty observations.', 2022, '0063204169', '9780063242401', 368, NULL, 676, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14809692-L.jpg', '/works/OL25382083W', NULL, '2022', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'remarkably-bright-creatures-shelby-van-pelt', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:42:58', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
